libmongo-client
------------------------------------------
This is an alternative C driver for MongoDB, with slightly different goals
than the official one:

libmongo-client is meant to be a stable (API, ABI and quality alike), clean,
well documented and well tested shared library, that strives to make the most
common use cases as convenient as possible.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.9-1
  libgcc1-4.5.3-2
  libglib2.0_0-2.28.8-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-10-1
  automake-4-10
  binutils-2.21.53-2
  cygport-0.10.5-1
  gawk-3.1.8-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.3-2
  libtool-2.4-1
  make-3.81-2

Canonical website:
  http://algernon.github.com/libmongo-client/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/algernon/libmongo-client.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libmongo-client-0.1.4+git20110909-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libmongo-client-0.1.4+git20110909-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libmongo-client-0.1.4+git20110909-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libmongo-client-0.1.4+git20110909-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libmongo-client0-0.1.4+git20110909-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libmongo-client-devel-0.1.4+git20110909-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

